    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-03-08T04:41:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-03-08T04:41:00-05:00" n="467"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d467">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 656.119/276</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_GJW1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Garrett</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">The Hague</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-03-08T10:00:00+00:19">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 8, 1918, 10 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 12.13 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2112. Minister for Foreign Affairs writes me that there are 65 Dutch ships in the
                    United States. Of these, 39 have now been duly chartered and confirmed by cable;
                    10 duly chartered but not yet confirmed by cable; 3, order to charter cabled but
                    no reply yet; 1 <pb facs="0571" n="1405" xml:id="pg_1405"/> offered for charter
                    but no answer received; 2 under German obligation owing to repairs with German
                    material, can therefore be chartered only for Belgian Relief or Switzerland; 5
                    ordered to unload, whereupon to be chartered; 1 passenger ship <hi rend="italic"
                        >Ryndam</hi> and 4 only [<hi rend="italic">others?</hi>] not yet agreed upon
                    as to charters. <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LJJ1">Loudon</persName>
                    adds that no cables have been received, for instance, by Netherlands Indian
                    lines which do not even know in which ports their ships are lying. <persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SLP1">Sheldon</persName> notified.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_GJW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Garrett</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
